Steps to run this:

Install Python if not already (python.org → check "Add to PATH" during install)
Open this folder in VS Code (File → Open Folder)
Open terminal in VS Code (Ctrl + `) and run:

   pip install pytesseract opencv-python-headless pillow

Download and install Tesseract OCR from: https://github.com/UB-Mannheim/tesseract/wiki
Open ocr_recognition.py, find this line near the top

   pytesseract.pytesseract.tesseract_cmd = r"C:\Program Files\Tesseract-OCR\tesseract.exe"
(make sure the path matches wherever Tesseract actually got installed on your PC)

6. In terminal, run:
   python make_sample.py
   python ocr_recognition.py
That's it, it'll print the recognized text and confidence score.

Note: Two png sample images provided for testing purposes.
